==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dodo
<hw>Do"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Dodoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Said to be fr. Pg.
<ets>doudo</ets> silly, foolish (cf. <er>Booby</er>); this is fr. Prov.
E. <ets>dold</ets>, the same word as E. <ets>dolt</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large, extinct bird (<spn>Didus
ineptus</spn>), formerly inhabiting the Island of Mauritius. It had
short, half-fledged wings, like those of the ostrich, and a short neck
and legs; -- called also <altname>dronte</altname>. It was related to
the pigeons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doe</ent>⟦br⟧
